Ad Text:
Shape the future of Market Data Services at the Bank

Are you a strategic, commercially minded leader with deep expertise in market data platforms and dealing room technologies? We're looking for an experienced Market Data Manager to lead the end-to-end management of market data services that powers the Reserve Bank of Australia. This permanent role offers the opportunity to guide a high performing team, influence strategic decisions, and strengthen the Bank's market data capabilities as our operating environment evolves.


The role

As Market Data Manager, you will lead the team responsible for the full lifecycle of market data services, including platform administration, contract management, vendor engagement, commercial optimisation and continuous service improvement. You will work closely with both business and technology stakeholders to ensure the Bank's market data capabilities are reliable, cost effective, and aligned to strategic priorities. This role requires a strong blend of technical expertise, commercial judgement and people leadership. You will also contribute to the broader leadership of Business Support Services, helping to foster a values aligned, collaborative, and high-performance culture.


Why join us?

This is an opportunity to step into a leadership role that sits at the intersection of technology, financial markets, and strategic delivery. You'll help shape the future direction of critical market data services at the Bank, working with industry leading vendors and stakeholders. The Financial Markets Group is responsible for implementing the Bank's domestic and foreign exchange operations, as well as analysing market developments and managing key institutional relationships. The Market Data team enables these activities by ensuring the reliable delivery and optimisation of market data services. You will work closely with internal stakeholders, technologists and vendors to deliver solutions that support the Bank's strategic objectives and solve complex market data challenges.


Key responsibilities

Lead the Market Data team, ensuring operational excellence across platforms, contracts and support services
Oversee the delivery, enhancement and reliability of market data systems, market connectivity and dealing room technologies
Build strong relationships and influence across both technical and business domains
Manage vendor relationships and commercial negotiations, ensuring cost effective and risk aware outcomes
Ensure robust governance, controls and risk management practices
Drive continuous improvement, innovation and operational efficiency
Provide coaching, mentoring and day to day direction to a high performing team


What we're looking for

We're seeking a capable, forward-looking leader who brings:


Strong experience with market data platforms, financial market systems or trading technology
Advanced knowledge of market data products, datasets, exchange connectivity or dealing room environments
Excellent stakeholder engagement skills, with the ability to influence across technical and non-technical teams
A strong commercial mindset with experience balancing cost, service quality and risk
Proven experience leading teams or mentoring in a collaborative, high performance environment
The ability to manage competing priorities and respond proactively to risks and opportunities
A continuous improvement mindset with an eye for process optimisation and service uplift


Be More

Working for an organisation that truly makes a difference to the people of Australia, we can offer development and career opportunities in a collaborative environment that supports your growth, wellbeing and promotes flexibility. Your individual growth and success drives the RBA forward as an organisation. Be more means you can do more, for yourself and for Australia.

Why RBA?

The RBA makes an important contribution to the Australian economy through the pursuit of national economic policy objectives and associated activities in financial markets and banking. We also issue Australia's banknotes and operate infrastructure critical to the payments system, all of which contribute to the welfare of the Australian people.

Made up of specialists across a wide range of fields, our people, values, and culture play a critical role in achieving our objectives. Striving to be Open & Dynamic, we consider and incorporate different perspectives, work across teams and are transparent with each other, whilst delivering quality together effectively and focusing on outcomes by prioritising, testing, learning, and refining as we go. Our people conduct themselves with a high degree of integrity, while striving for excellence in the work they perform and the outcomes they achieve. We encourage intelligent inquiry, and we treat one another with respect while promoting the public interest through our efforts. We know it is the growth and success of our people that drives the RBA forward.

Come and make a bigger contribution while you build and develop your own skills too, because being more means you can do more, for yourself and for Australia.

The Reserve Bank of Australia is committed to equity, diversity and inclusion through key initiatives. We welcome and encourage applicants from diverse backgrounds to apply, including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, culturally and linguistically diverse background, those living with a disability and from the LGBTQ+ community. We are committed to making the recruitment process fair and equitable for all our candidates.

At ASIC, you can be the change that ensures a fair, strong and efficient financial system for the benefit of all Australians. Contribute to delivering on ASIC's purpose, vision, and strategic priorities to help maintain the integrity of the financial system and protect consumers from harm.

 

Sydney, Melbourne or Traralgon locations. Other locations may be considered.
Salary from $152,074 - $168,164 (depending upon experience) + 15.4% super
24 Month Fixed Term Contract
Applications close at 11:59pm AEDT, 6 March 2026

 

The team 

The Registry Connect program is focused on the stabilisation and targeted uplift of business registers including designing connections to the ABN and Director ID registers held by the ATO, and the more than 30 registers held by ASIC.

 

The role

As a Learning & Capability Lead, you will lead the design, governance and delivery of a program-wide learning and capability strategy that enables ASIC staff and external stakeholders to successfully transition to modernised registry services.

 

You will be accountable for:

 

Leading the development and execution of the RegistryConnect learning and capability strategy, ensuring alignment with program and organisational goals
Shaping and governing the program's learning ecosystem, including capability standards, quality benchmarks and evaluation frameworks
Providing expert advice to senior executives and stakeholders on learning risks, opportunities and capability requirements
Overseeing program‑wide learning activities, including training needs analysis, learning design, content development and delivery planning, with hands‑on support as needed
Overseeing development and maintenance of learning materials (user guides, eLearning, simulations, walkthroughs, knowledge articles) incorporating user‑centred design, adult‑learning and accessibility principles
Defining success measures and implementing structured evaluation for capability uplift, learning effectiveness, adoption and proficiency
Representing the learning and capability function in program forums, steering committees and governance meetings

 

About you

You will have extensive experience designing and executing learning strategies for large‑scale transformations or programs. In addition you will have strong leadership capability, including coaching and developing learning professionals.  Other skills will include:

 

Tertiary qualifications in learning and development, education, organisational development, change management or a related discipline
Demonstrated experience leading training needs analysis, learning design and capability uplift in complex environments
Proven ability to develop diverse learning materials, including eLearning, simulations, guided training and knowledge content
Experience applying adult‑learning principles, human‑centred design and accessibility standards
Demonstrated ability to manage complex stakeholder relationships, influence senior leaders and navigate sensitive capability issues
Excellent analytical skills to identify workforce risks and design capability solutions
Advanced communication skills to translate complex program information into clear, effective learning
Experience working within governance and compliance frameworks to ensure quality and integrity of learning artefacts

 

View the position description for more information or click ‘apply' to start your application. Applications close at 11:59pm AEDT, 6 March 2026.

 

About ASIC

ASIC's remit is one of the broadest of regulators across the world. ASIC regulates corporations, markets, financial services and consumer credit and monitors and promotes market integrity and consumer protection in the Australian financial system. Through our enforcement work, we hold to account those who contravene the law, working to achieve strong outcomes that address the greatest consumer and investor harms.

 

ASIC is an equal opportunity employer seeking people who want to make a difference. ASIC is committed to providing a diverse and inclusive workplace where the very best talent in Australia chooses to work. Applications from people of all ages, cultural backgrounds, abilities, LGBTIQ+ identity, and people of Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander decent are encouraged to apply.

 

We offer a range of employee benefits including:

Attractive superannuation
Additional leave entitlements
50/50 hybrid work-from home model
Flexible work arrangements
Assistance for study and professional development

 

To work with us, you need to be an Australian citizen and be prepared to complete an ASIC Suitability and Baseline Assessment.

Contract until end of June | Hybrid (3 days onsite)

We are seeking an experienced Business Process Analyst to support a large transformation program within a well established financial services organisation.

This contract will run through to the end of June and offers a hybrid working model (3 days onsite, 2 days WFH).

The Role This position is focused on documenting and analysing current-state (as-is) processes to support broader transformation and re-engineering initiatives.

You will:

Document and analyse end-to-end business processes and workflows
Gather process performance data and identify pain points and inefficiencies
Develop high-quality process models aligned to established modelling standards
Facilitate workshops and work closely with business and technical stakeholders
Deliver approved and standardised artefacts within agreed timeframes
Identify opportunities for simplification, automation and continuous improvement
You will bring:

Proven experience as a Business Process Analyst / Process Analyst
Strong expertise in BPMN 2.0 and process modelling tools (e.g. Signavio, BizzDesign)
Experience working in complex, detail-heavy environments
Excellent stakeholder engagement and workshop facilitation skills
Strong analytical capability and ability to translate SME input into clear process maps
Financial services experience highly regarded
This is a great opportunity to contribute to a meaningful transformation initiative in a collaborative, outcomes-focused environment.

If this sounds like you, please apply or reach out for a confidential discussion.

Queensland Airports Limited (QAL) is an accomplished airport operator which owns and operates Gold Coast, Townsville, Longreach and Mount Isa airports – connecting the Gold Coast and northern NSW, along with regional Queensland, to the rest of the country and beyond. Our company has a vision to engage customers, connect communities and deliver exceptional experiences – and a commitment to delivering for the communities where we operate. We have been formally recognised as a ‘Great Place to Work – Certified’ organisation four times and recently was awarded Work180 accreditation as a champion for gender equity for the second year in a row. Our company is dedicated to a target of net zero Scope 1 and Scope 2 emissions by 2030. 

There has never been a better time to join us. 

 

What you’ll contribute to 

You’ll play a meaningful role in shaping the future of our aviation partnerships and commercial growth. Working collaboratively with colleagues across the business, you’ll help translate data, insights and market trends into thoughtful recommendations that support sustainable, long-term decision-making. 

Through your work, you’ll contribute to: 

Building and nurturing strong airline and aviation partnerships grounded in trust, transparency and shared outcomes 

Supporting strategic growth initiatives through well considered analysis and insight 

Enabling the organisation to make informed, balanced commercial decisions that consider both performance and people 

Bringing clarity and structure to complex information so others can move forward with confidence 

Your contribution will be valued not only for what you deliver, but for the care, curiosity and collaboration you bring to the way you work with others. 

 

How will you make an impact? 

You’ll make an impact by combining analytical thinking with genuine relationship buildingg skills. In this role, you’ll be trusted to explore opportunities, ask meaningful questions and support better outcomes through insight and collaboration. 

You’ll do this by: 

Possessing 3 to 5 years’ experience as an airline/airport analyst and have a tertiary qualification in aviation, economics or research 

Analysing commercial, operational and market data to uncover trends, risks and opportunities 

Working closely with internal stakeholders to understand priorities, challenges and emerging needs 

Supporting business cases, proposals and performance reviews with clear, well-structured analysis 

Contributing to aviation strategy by balancing commercial outcomes with long-term sustainability and partnership value 

Presenting insights in a clear, accessible way that supports informed decision-making 

Your ability to listen, connect perspectives and communicate with clarity will help turn information into action and strategy into real-world impact. 

 

What we offer you 

This is an opportunity to be part of a progressive organisation with a great culture and assist in the transformation and growth of the business. Flexible working options are available for all employees. At QAL, we uphold the philosophy that the smooth integration of life and work benefits all. We call it ‘Living Well’. 

QAL supports an inclusive approach and values diversity within the workplace. We aim to provide opportunities that allow individuals to reach their full potential regardless of their background, gender, age, work status, religious or cultural identity. Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples are encouraged to apply. 

The successful candidate will be required to adhere to QAL’s Drug and Alcohol Management Plan (DAMP), which includes pre-employment Drug and Alcohol Testing and have the ability to obtain an Aviation Security Identification Card (ASIC).

Internal Audit is building the future of data enabled assurance.
Build products that materially strengthen audit assurance.
Be trusted to set direction, coach technical team, and drive meaningful outcomes.

Our people are customer obsessed. They prioritise the needs and satisfaction of the customer above all else. ?Our mindset fosters innovation and creates strong, lasting customer relationships as we strive to be the most customer centric company in Australia and New Zealand. 

In the role of Senior Audit Manager, you will join Internal Audit team that’s doubling down on winning together.

Each day you will go above and beyond to:

Lead a multidisciplinary team of data professionals, ensuring Internal Audit has reliable, scalable and well governed data products that directly support audit planning, execution and insight generation.
Provide end to end delivery and operational excellence of Internal Audit’s data pipelines, continuous assurance capabilities and reporting products.
Own and oversee the design, development and operation of pipelines, datasets, transformations, models and reporting products.
Provide hands on technical leadership setting and embedding clear engineering, reporting and quality standards. 
Drive uplift in delivery maturity, ways of working and agile practices across the team. 
Partner closely with a wide range of technical and non-technical stakeholders within Audit and across the Enterprise.

What you’ll bring

Substantial years of experience in multidisciplinary engineering and reporting teams, with experience in people leadership roles. 
Deep technical capability across Databricks, Python, SQL, Power BI, Git/GitHub.
Strong grounding in data modelling, ETL/ELT and DevOps concepts. 
A track record of building robust, scalable and well governed data and reporting products.
Excellent project management and communication skills, with the ability to translate complex technical concepts for nontechnical stakeholders. 
Experience in banking, audit or risk is beneficial but not essential — curiosity, judgement and leadership matter most.

We respectfully ask candidates to hold any questions for the phone interview, where we’ll discuss the role in detail and answer any questions. This helps to ensure a focussed, efficient and fair application process. The talent acquisition team looks forward to addressing all inquiries at that time if your application progresses. 

A diverse and inclusive workplace works better for everyone 

We know that our people make us who we are. That's why we have built a culture of equity and respect – where everyone feels valued and appreciated for being their authentic selves. In partnership with our multiple Employee Resource Groups (ERGs) we continue to foster an inclusive environment, where all NAB colleagues’ unique backgrounds and identities are understood, respected and celebrated. 

We are committed to providing an environment where you can work your way.

Immediate hands-on capability with Microsoft Fabric and Power BI is essential
We are seeking an experienced Analyst Programmer to support the development and delivery of an Case Management Service (CMS) platform solution. This role will play a critical part in delivering a minimum viable product (MVP) within a tight timeframe, leveraging Microsoft Fabric, Power BI, and data analytics to provide meaningful insights and progress reporting to stakeholders.

Key Responsibilities
Support the development and implementation of a Case Management Service platform using Microsoft Fabric and associated technologies
Undertake data analysis and analytical projects related to the Roadmap CMS platform
Design, build and maintain Power BI dashboards and reports to visually present insights on progress, trends and common challenges
Work with stakeholders to understand reporting requirements and translate them into effective data visualisations
Essential Requirements 

Data analytical capability, proficient in Excel, Power BI
Experience with Microsoft Fabric will be highly regarded
How to Apply

If you're ready to take on the next challenge in your career and you think you can bring your passion to this exciting role, then please click on 'Apply Now' to submit your cover letter and resume. For specific questions relating to the role please contract Nick at nraicevich@genesisit.com.au.

Diversity and inclusion are strongly supported at Genesis IT Recruitment. People of all nationalities, gender identities, and cultural backgrounds, including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander Peoples, are encouraged to apply.

Join RiskLogic and Help Build a More Resilient Tomorrow!

At RiskLogic, our vision is simple but powerful: to work with inspired people to build meaningful organisations that contribute to a better tomorrow. Every day, we empower our clients to navigate the most challenging situations with confidence. Through the right tools, training and experience, we help strengthen resilience maturity across organisations that shape our communities.

Who We Are

RiskLogic is a market‑leading consulting firm supporting corporate, not‑for‑profit and government clients across Australia.

Our culture is grounded in our values — Integrity, Passion, Innovation and Performance — and brought to life through our CREATE principles: Collaboration, Respect, Evolutionary, Accountable, Transparent and Enjoyable.

Our people come to work knowing they make a real, measurable difference in a constantly evolving threat environment.

About the Role

We are seeking a dynamic leader to support regional growth initiatives, drive performance, oversee high‑quality service delivery, and champion the wellbeing and development of our people. You will play a key role in upholding RiskLogic’s purpose, values and brand while ensuring exceptional outcomes for our clients. This role will work closely with the Head of Resilience at RiskLogic and deliver on large and complex programs of work.

Key Responsibilities

Operational

Manage and contribute to daily client deliverables across business continuity, crisis management, incident and emergency management.

Lead activities including program reviews, policy and framework development, BIAs, threat assessments, workshops, training design and facilitation, exercises, and technology configuration.

Build and maintain strong client relationships across diverse sectors.

Support local strategic alliances and partnerships.

Contribute to quality management and continuous improvement initiatives.

Collaborate across the Group to deliver integrated outcomes and identify cross‑sell opportunities.

Service clients across Australia, with interstate and occasional overseas travel.

Participate in negotiations, forecasting and managing client challenges.

Support performance management processes and other operational requirements.

People Leadership

Lead and support the performance of direct reports.

Help set and achieve key performance goals within the team.

Provide coaching, mentoring and ongoing feedback to support capability development.

Contribute to workforce planning and team growth initiatives.

What You Bring

Minimum 5 years’ experience delivering relevant services, ideally within consulting.

Expertise in at business continuity, crisis management and/or operational resilience.

Strong experience facilitating training sessions and exercises.

Proven ability to build trusted relationships at all levels.

Exceptional leadership, project management and organisational skills.

Strong problem‑solving capability and the ability to influence outcomes.

Commercial acumen and a performance‑driven mindset.

Ability to adapt to diverse environments and manage multiple priorities.

Excellent written and verbal communication skills.

A commitment to continuous improvement and quality delivery.

Self‑motivation and the ability to work effectively with remote teams.

A genuine desire for personal and team growth.




If you’re passionate about resilience, leadership and making a meaningful impact, we’d love to hear from you.

Please submit your resume and cover letter. We will be reaching out to shortlisted candidates shortly.

About Us

We're an established and growing non-bank lender specialising in providing flexible, customer-focused financial solutions to Australian SMEs. With an emphasis on innovation, data-driven decision-making, and a collaborative culture, we're continuing to invest in our digital and operational transformation.

The Role

We're looking for a Business Analyst to join our delivery team and play a key role in the implementation of a new Loan Origination platform. This role will suit someone who thrives in a hands-on environment - comfortable gathering requirements, validating requirements, managing the vendor and has proven experience driving continuous improvement in our Agile framework.

You'll work across technology, product, and operations to ensure initiatives are delivered efficiently, business outcomes are clear, and projects are delivered on time.

Key Responsibilities

Lead the elicitation, documentation, validation, and management of business and functional requirements.
Conduct requirements and scope reviews to ensure alignment with business goals.
Track and manage changes to requirements and scope throughout the project lifecycle.
Validate requirements and ensure traceability from initiation through to delivery.
Perform gap and change analysis to support business decision-making.
Provide strategic recommendations to senior stakeholders based on analysis and findings.
Experienced working with development teams.

About You

Seasoned Business Analyst expertise within financial services or lending.
System experience across Loan Origination, CRM, Credit systems and servicing.
Strong stakeholder engagement and facilitation skills.
Ability to balance structure and flexibility in a growing, fast-moving organisation.
Practical understanding of technology delivery (experience with Jira or similar tools a plus).

This role is 5 days in office.

About Us
Animal Emergency Australia (AEA) is a network of 24/7 emergency veterinary hospitals, general practices, and support services across the country. We’re here to help veterinary professionals do and be their best — delivering high-quality care, education, and innovation. At AEA, we believe that behind every great vet team is a great support team — and that’s where you come in.

About the Role
The Commercial Strategy and Analytics Lead shapes and governs the commercial intelligence that underpins AEA’s most important strategic and operational decisions. The role exists to define what “good” looks like economically, guide sustainable growth and capital allocation, and translate pricing, workforce, and investment decisions into clear commercial outcomes. It blends strategic problem-solving, financial modelling, and advanced analytics to cut through noise and establish a defensible, data-led view of performance across the network.

Acting as the single source of commercial truth, this role owns enterprise commercial models, assumptions, and Business Intelligence strategy. It enables evidence-based decision-making by Executives and the Board and has the authority to challenge decisions not supported by data. While final decisions sit with leadership, this role is accountable for the quality, integrity, and coherence of the insights that inform them—allowing leaders to focus on deciding, not debating the data.

This is a full-time hybrid role based out of our Animal Emergency Australia Springwood office.

Key Responsibilities

Own long-term growth, capacity and investment models to guide network expansion, capital allocation and Board-level decisions.
Lead data-driven pricing and margin analysis, translating complex commercial trade-offs into clear, evidence-based decisions.
Develop workforce and remuneration models to support scalable growth, productivity improvements and informed people planning.
Provide rigorous commercial and financial modelling for major strategic initiatives, acting as a trusted internal advisory resource.
Own the BI strategy and tools, ensuring consistent metrics, strong governance, and executive-ready insights across the organisation.
Turn complex analysis into clear, actionable insights that strengthen executive decision-making and analytical maturity.

About You

Ex-consulting, commercial or pricing strategy background with strong commercial problem-solving discipline.
5–8+ years in strategy, commercial analytics, FP&A, or enterprise analytics roles.
Advanced financial modelling capability (long-range, scenario, sensitivity).
Strong BI and analytics fluency (Power BI essential; Anaplan highly desirable).
Comfortable operating across ambiguity, senior stakeholders, and competing priorities.
Credibility to challenge executives with evidence, not opinion.
Interested in an enterprise decision-enablement role (this is not a reporting role)

Why Join Us

Competitive salary approximately $160, 000 + Super + 17.5% annual leave loading
Hybrid work options available (initial training in Springwood office)
Join Australia’s largest employee-owned veterinary group 
Access to Fitness Passport 
Pet well-being discounts up to 50% off + $0 Examinations 
Dedicated wellbeing committee for our employees (Mental health first aid certifications, flu vaccinations, podcasts, etc.)   
Access to our Employee Assistance Program (psychology, nutrition, sleep)   
Refer a Friend Program & Rewards (up to $2000!) 
Further education & career planning benefits

Click apply today to join Animal Emergency Australia and make a difference in the lives of pets and pet owners across Australia!
